`0Help for the Line Edit Menu ------------------

<C> Continue Msg  - This option allows you to continue typing your message
                    on the last line of your message.
<E> Edit Line     - This option allows you to edit a specified line.  You
                    can replace a certain character string in the line.
<D> Delete Line   - This option allows you to delete a full line in your
                    message.
<I> Insert Line   - This option allows you to insert a line somewhere in
                    your message.
<R> Replace Line  - This option erases a specified line and lets you
                    retype the WHOLE line.
<<> Left-justify  - This option will left-justify a line flush left.
<^> Center line   - This option will center a line.
<>> Right-justify - This option will right-justify a line flush right.
<L> List Message  - This option displays the full message that you have
                    typed in.
<S> Save Message  - This option saves the message you have typed and then
                    exits the message editor.
<A> Abort Message - This aborts and exits the message you are typing
                    WITHOUT saving it.

Press ENTER to continue....`4
